A fabulous off-side six by Dinesh Karthik helped India beat Bangladesh by 4 wickets in the final of the Nidahas Trophy at the Khettarama Stadium, Colombo.Karthik came to the crease after the loss of India's 5th wicket and then India needed 34 runs off 12 balls.He struck 22 runs off the penultimate over bowled by Rubel Hossain.Then the equation came down to 5 off the last bowl.He hit Soumya Sarkar over the extra cover boundary to deny Bangladesh the victory.Karthik made 29 not out off 8 balls.Rohit Sharma top scored for India with 56 off 42 balls.